description: first sequence
second sequence
third sequence - creates the NSP2 protein
fourth sequence - creates the NSP3 protein which cuts loose other viral proteins and removes tags from proteins that should be degraded
fifth sequence - creates the NSP4 protein which builds fluid-filled bubbles within infected cells
sixth sequence - creates the NSP5 protein which cuts out proteins to carry out other jobs
NSP6 - creates virus factory bubbles
Creates NSP7 (works with NSP8) - creates new copies of the RNA
Creates NSP8 (works with NSP7) - creates new copies of the RNA
Creates NSP9 infiltrates tiny channels in the infected cell’s nucleus
Creates NSP10 - Genetic Camouflage. This protein works with NSP16 to camouflage the virus’s genes so that they don’t get attacked
Creates NSP12 - protein assembles genetic letters into new virus genomes
Creates NSP13 - Potentially used to unwind RNA
Creates NSP14 - virus proofreading
Creates NSP15 - suspect that this protein chops up leftover virus RNA as a way to hide from the infected cell’s antiviral defenses
Creates NSP16 - Camouflage - works with NSP10 to help the virus’s genes hide from proteins that chop up viral RNA.
Spike protein - binds virus protein into human cells

Escape Artist · ORF3a - help change the environment inside the infected cell to make it easier for the virus to replicate. This one pokes a hole in the membrane of an infected cell, making it easier for new viruses to escape
Envelope Protein - helps form the oily bubble of the virus
Membrane Protein - forms part of the outer coat of the virus
Signal Blocker · ORF6 - blocks signals that the infected cell would send out to the immune system
Virus Liberator · ORF7a - cuts down an infected cell’s supply of tetherin, allowing more of the viruses to escape
ORF8 Mystery Protein
Nucleocapsid Protein · N - protects the virus RNA, keeping it stable inside the virus
Mystery Protein · ORF10 - mystery protein. No one knows what does this yet
Ending sequence - terminates protein making
Full sequence - variant 1
Full sequence - variant 2
